---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageMeta from '@/components/PageMeta.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Governance"
  description="How OPDA is governed: UK initiative context, ToIP framework, conformance, change management, lifecycle, risk."
>
<PageMeta category="Section overview" variant="brand" updated="Updated 2026-05-17" />

      <h1>Governance</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        How OPDA is governed, who governs it, the UK government initiative it sits
        inside, and the published rules that make the standard authoritative. PDTF
        follows the Trust Over IP four-layer model, with the wider context defined by
        the Digital Markets, Competition and Consumers Act 2024 and coordinated through
        the Digital Property Market Steering Group.
      </p>

      <h2 id="uk-initiative-context">UK initiative context</h2>
      <p>The legislation, departments, and forums that frame OPDA's mandate.</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <a class="card" href="/governance/uk-initiative">
          <div class="pill pill--brand">Start here</div>
          <h3>UK initiative — overview</h3>
          <p>Five-tier map: legislation → departments → forums → delivery → standards.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/legislation">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Policy</div>
          <h3>Legislation &amp; policy</h3>
          <p>DMCC Act 2024, DUA Act 2025, Leasehold &amp; Freehold Reform Act, Industrial Strategy.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/departments">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Policy</div>
          <h3>Departments &amp; bodies</h3>
          <p>MHCLG, DSIT, DBT, HMLR, NTSELAT, FCA, ICO — who does what.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/steering-forums">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Policy</div>
          <h3>Steering &amp; coordination</h3>
          <p>DPMSG (13 founding members), Smart Data Council, HBSG.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="opda-organisation">OPDA the organisation</h2>
      <p>Who OPDA is, and the operational vehicle it delivers through.</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <a class="card" href="/governance/opda-members">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Members</div>
          <h3>OPDA member firms</h3>
          <p>13 founding members + association members, mapped to bounded contexts. One simple membership tier.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/sandbox">
          <div class="pill pill--success">Delivery</div>
          <h3>Trust Framework Sandbox</h3>
          <p>CLC + OPDA + Raidiam, RPF-funded. Operational today.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="standards-landscape">Standards landscape</h2>
      <p>How PDTF anchors itself to external trust and data-governance frameworks.</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <a class="card" href="/governance/toip-governance">
          <div class="pill pill--accent">Alignment</div>
          <h3>ToIP governance model</h3>
          <p>The 4 layers, mapped to OPDA's artefacts. Why ToIP fits a federated trust framework.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/strategic-alignment">
          <div class="pill pill--accent">Alignment</div>
          <h3>Strategic alignment</h3>
          <p>HMLR Strategy 2022+, DSIT National Data Strategy, DIATF, W3C VC, ToIP — how PDTF aligns.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="opda-rules">OPDA's rules</h2>
      <p>The published rules and procedures that make OPDA's standard authoritative.</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <a class="card" href="/governance/conformance-scheme">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Rules</div>
          <h3>Conformance &amp; certification</h3>
          <p>Self-certification today (3-person panel, 80% pass mark). Planned technical conformance follows the Open Banking pattern.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/accreditation-directory">
          <div class="pill pill--brand">Rules · new</div>
          <h3>Accreditation Directory</h3>
          <p>Two-axis maturity view per member firm — AL coverage + capability scores. Full spec in ADR 0004.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/change-management">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Rules</div>
          <h3>Change management</h3>
          <p>Two pathways: constitutional change (General Assembly, 30-day notice) and technical change (8-step SOP).</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/lifecycle-versioning">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Rules</div>
          <h3>Lifecycle &amp; versioning</h3>
          <p>PDTF schemas v3.5.0 (semver). Deprecation policy still in design.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/risk-liability">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Rules</div>
          <h3>Risk &amp; liability</h3>
          <p>Articles cap member liability at £1; framework spec is MIT/AS-IS. Downstream liability still open.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="operating-model">Operating Model</h2>
      <p>How the framework runs day-to-day: who's accountable, when meetings happen, who engages with stakeholders, how unstructured attachments flow. Adopts DCAM v3's "Operating Model" component name directly.</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <a class="card" href="/governance/data-stewardship">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Operating</div>
          <h3>Data stewardship &amp; decision rights</h3>
          <p>Domain Data Stewards (one per bounded context), RACI for the 8-step SOP, decision rights matrix, and voting mechanics grounded in the Articles.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/meetings-and-feedback">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Operating</div>
          <h3>Meeting cadence &amp; feedback</h3>
          <p>Volunteer-paced SLAs, 6-week breaking-change consultations on Astro+Artalk pages, 10-year decision log, and the topic-flagging convention for EC stewards.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/stakeholder-engagement">
          <div class="pill pill--info">Operating</div>
          <h3>Stakeholder engagement</h3>
          <p>Five engagement modes — members, non-member firms, regulators, government, consumers. FCA via PRISM, Which? as consumer voice, devolved-nations engagement active.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/overlay-attachments">
          <div class="pill pill--brand">Operating · new</div>
          <h3>Overlay attachments</h3>
          <p>Per-attachment policy across v3 overlays (TA10 plans, EPCs, leasehold packs, photographs). File formats, signing, retention, consent.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="quality-security">Quality &amp; security</h2>
      <p>Cross-cutting frameworks every member firm reports against. Fills the two largest gaps in OPDA's published rules (per ADR 0001).</p>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <a class="card" href="/governance/data-quality">
          <div class="pill pill--brand">Quality · new</div>
          <h3>Data quality framework</h3>
          <p>Six dimensions — accuracy, completeness, consistency, timeliness, uniqueness, validity. Per-claim measurement; quarterly reporting via the Accreditation Directory.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/governance/data-security">
          <div class="pill pill--brand">Security · new</div>
          <h3>Data security framework</h3>
          <p>KYC/KYB, DID key management, signature verification, revocation, audit logging. Policy + checklist + audit profile per control.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

